				\begin{document}
$$ {F}_{\mathrm{NORM}}\left[t\right]={F}_{\mathrm{ROI},\mathrm{CORR}}\left[t\right]\times \left(1/{F}_{\mathrm{ROI},\mathrm{B}\mathrm{G}}\left[0\right]\right) $$
\end{document}FNORM[t]=FROI,CORR[t]×(1/FROI,BG[0])
. We would like torecommend the investigator to consult reference [19] for more comprehensive in depth details on both FRAP and FLIP imaging approaches and data analysis.8.Calculate the F
1/2 using formula (5) and determine the corresponding time point on the x-axis of the FR graph to determine t
1/2.
